title: 12/21/23 Joint Study Committee on Service Delivery Strategies
summary:
## Overview

This transcript appears to be from a joint study committee meeting on service delivery strategies in Georgia, with minimal substantive legislative activity. The key focus was on approving a list of seven recommendations, which was described as a framework for future legislation rather than legislation itself.

## Key Actions
None detected.

## Bills Introduced (First Reading)
None detected.

## Notable Moments
- The committee members discussed establishing a quorum and technical difficulties with one member joining the virtual meeting.
- The committee chair thanked the staff for their work in preparing the list of recommendations.
- The committee adopted the list of seven recommendations unanimously.
- The committee chair wished everyone a Merry Christmas at the end of the meeting.

## Votes
The committee voted unanimously to adopt the list of seven recommendations.

## Attendance
The committee had a quorum of at least five members, including the two co-chairs.

The meeting was adjourned after the vote on the recommendations. The next session date was not specified.
